# Asset Locations

## Context
The repo keeps assets grouped by consumer so paths stay predictable.

## Rules for adding/updating assets
- all logo MUST be added in public/icons/ directory, and referenced from there
- Runtime/static assets go in `public/` (or `examples/**/public/` for examples) and are referenced from the public root.
- Docs images live in `dev-docs/docs/assets/` and are referenced with relative MDX paths.
- Docusaurus site chrome images live in `dev-docs/static/img/`.
- Font sources live in `packages/excalidraw/fonts/`, and raw TTF inputs live in `scripts/woff2/assets/`.
- README/badge assets live in `.github/assets/`.
- When self-hosting fonts/assets, serve them from a public path and set `window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH` to that base.

## How to verify
- Confirm new assets are placed under the expected directory for their consumer.
- Ensure references resolve (MDX relative paths, public URLs, `EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH`).
- Run the relevant app/docs build for the area you touched.
